text: Fantastic Fried carrot cake aka char kueh. Huge portion for the $3.50 option although it was served in a tiny plate. Great tasting carrot cake. Kudos to the young gentleman behind the wok for carrying on the traditional local culinary delight. Highly recommended.

Kway Chap $2.50
HOKI COFFEESHOP
150 Bishan St.11, S570150

Other than famous $2.50 kway chap stall at Jalan Batu HC, we found another hidden kway chap stall that sells for only $2.50 in this happening neighbourhood.

We enjoyed the local food here. All nice. For video please visit YouTube = Little Red in a Big World.

Went this morning and decided to eat the fried carrot cake (black). Still good and serving is generous for price of $3.50. You can order black and white (mix) if you order large one that cost $5.00.

Go try when you are there. Really not bad.
Nice Prata to have for late lunch. They make when there is order. Prata will be freshly made n hot...
